  "prompt": "Why isn\u2019t Pok\u00e9mon GO working?",
  "response": "Pok\u00e9mon GO can experience issues for a variety of reasons. Here's a breakdown of common causes and how to troubleshoot them:\n\n**1. Server-Side Issues (Most Common, Often Temporary):**\n\n*   **Niantic Server Outages:** This is the most frequent cause. Niantic's servers might be down for maintenance, updates, or due to unexpected traffic spikes (like during events or new releases).\n    *   **How to Check:**\n        *   **Official Pok\u00e9mon GO Twitter:** Check the official Pok\u00e9mon GO Twitter account (@PokemonGoApp) for announcements about server status.\n        *   **DownDetector:** Visit DownDetector (search \"DownDetector Pokemon GO\") to see if other users are reporting outages.\n        *   **Reddit:** The r/pokemongo subreddit is often a good source of information about widespread issues.\n    *   **Solution:** If it's a server-side issue, there's nothing you can do except wait for Niantic to resolve the problem. Try again later.\n\n**2. Your Internet Connection:**\n\n*   **Poor Wi-Fi or Mobile Data:** A weak or unstable internet connection is a common culprit.\n    *   **How to Check:**\n        *   **Test your connection:** Try browsing the web or using other apps that require internet.\n        *   **Signal strength:** Look at the Wi-Fi or mobile data signal strength indicator on your phone.\n    *   **Solution:**\n        *   **Switch between Wi-Fi and mobile data:** Try connecting to a different network.  Sometimes one works better than the other.\n        *   **Move closer to your Wi-Fi router:** If you're using Wi-Fi, ensure you have a strong signal.\n        *   **Restart your router:** A simple router restart can often fix connectivity problems.\n        *   **Check your data plan:** Make sure you haven't exceeded your data limit.\n\n**3. GPS Issues:**\n\n*   **Weak GPS Signal:** Pok\u00e9mon GO relies heavily on GPS for location tracking. If your phone has trouble getting a good GPS signal, the game won't work correctly.\n    *   **How to Check:**\n        *   **Outdoors vs. Indoors:** GPS signals are weaker indoors. Try going outside to see if that helps.\n        *   **Other GPS Apps:** Test other apps that use GPS, like Google Maps or Waze, to see if they're working correctly.\n    *   **Solution:**\n        *   **Go outdoors:** Ensure you have a clear view of the sky.\n        *   **Restart your device:** A reboot can sometimes refresh the GPS connection.\n        *   **Check GPS settings:**\n            *   **Android:** Go to Settings > Location and make sure Location Services are turned on and set to \"High accuracy\" or \"Device only\" (depending on your Android version).\n            *   **iOS:** Go to Settings > Privacy > Location Services and make sure Location Services are turned on and Pok\u00e9mon GO is set to \"Always\" or \"While Using the App.\"\n        *   **Calibrate your GPS (Android):** Some Android phones have a GPS calibration feature. You might need to wave your phone in a figure-eight motion.  Search online for instructions specific to your phone model.\n\n**4. App Issues:**\n\n*   **Outdated App Version:** Make sure you're using the latest version of Pok\u00e9mon GO from the App Store (iOS) or Google Play Store (Android).\n    *   **How to Check:**\n        *   **App Store/Play Store:** Go to the App Store or Play Store and search for Pok\u00e9mon GO. If an \"Update\" button is available, tap it.\n    *   **Solution:** Update the app to the latest version.\n*   **Corrupted App Data:** Sometimes the app's data can become corrupted, leading to errors.\n    *   **Solution:**\n        *   **Clear App Cache (Android):** Go to Settings > Apps > Pok\u00e9mon GO > Storage > Clear Cache.\n        *   **Clear App Data (Android):**  Go to Settings > Apps > Pok\u00e9mon GO > Storage > Clear Data.  **Warning: This will reset your app settings and you'll have to log in again.**\n        *   **Reinstall the App (Both Android and iOS):** Delete the app from your device and then download and install it again from the App Store or Play Store. **This is a more drastic step but often solves the problem.**\n*   **App Conflicts:**  Rarely, other apps on your phone can interfere with Pok\u00e9mon GO.\n    *   **Solution:**  Try closing other apps that are running in the background.\n\n**5. Device Issues:**\n\n*   **Outdated Operating System:** Make sure your phone's operating system (Android or iOS) is up to date. Pok\u00e9mon GO may not be compatible with older operating systems.\n    *   **How to Check:**\n        *   **Android:** Go to Settings > About Phone > Software Update.\n        *   **iOS:** Go to Settings > General > Software Update.\n    *   **Solution:** Update your operating system to the latest version.\n*   **Insufficient Storage:** If your phone is running low on storage space, it can affect app performance.\n    *   **How to Check:** Go to your phone's settings to check your available storage space.\n    *   **Solution:** Free up storage space by deleting unused apps, photos, videos, and files.\n*   **Overheating:** If your phone is overheating, it can cause apps to malfunction.\n    *   **Solution:** Let your phone cool down before trying to play Pok\u00e9mon GO again.  Avoid playing in direct sunlight for extended periods.\n*   **Rooted/Jailbroken Device:** Pok\u00e9mon GO may not work properly on rooted (Android) or jailbroken (iOS) devices.\n    *   **Solution:** Unroot or unjailbreak your device (this is a complex process and may void your warranty).\n\n**6. Account Issues:**\n\n*   **Banned Account:** If you've violated the Pok\u00e9mon GO Terms of Service, your account may be banned.\n    *   **Solution:** Contact Niantic support to appeal the ban (if you believe it was issued in error).\n*   **Login Problems:** Problems with your Google or Pok\u00e9mon Trainer Club account can prevent you from logging in.\n    *   **Solution:**\n        *   **Verify your login credentials:** Make sure you're using the correct username and password.\n        *   **Reset your password:** If you've forgotten your password, reset it.\n        *   **Check your Google account permissions:** Ensure Pok\u00e9mon GO has the necessary permissions to access your Google account.\n\n**7. Niantic Known Issues:**\n\n*  **Check the Niantic Known Issues Page:** Niantic maintains a page listing known issues with their games, including Pokemon Go. Check this for known bugs and when to expect a fix.\n\n**Troubleshooting Steps - In Order of Simplicity:**\n\n1.  **Check Server Status:**  First, check if it's a widespread server issue.\n2.  **Restart the App:** Close Pok\u00e9mon GO completely and reopen it.\n3.  **Restart Your Device:** A simple reboot can often resolve minor glitches.\n4.  **Check Your Internet Connection:** Switch between Wi-Fi and mobile data.\n5.  **Check GPS Settings and Signal:** Ensure location services are enabled and you have a good GPS signal.\n6.  **Update the App:** Make sure you're using the latest version.\n7.  **Clear App Cache (Android Only):**  Try this before clearing data.\n8.  **Clear App Data (Android Only) or Reinstall the App:** This is a more drastic step, but often effective.  Remember to log in again.\n9.  **Update Your Operating System:** Check for OS updates.\n10. **Contact Niantic Support:** If none of the above steps work, contact Niantic support for assistance.\n\nWhen reporting an issue to Niantic or asking for help online, be sure to provide the following information:\n\n*   **Your device model (e.g., iPhone 13, Samsung Galaxy S23)**\n*   **Your operating system version (e.g., iOS 16, Android 13)**\n*   **The version of Pok\u00e9mon GO you're using**\n*   **A detailed description of the problem you're experiencing**\n*   **Any error messages you're seeing**\n\nGood luck troubleshooting!\n",
